                    <body>
                              <pb n="1"/>
                              <p rend="align(right)">
                                        <placeName>Barcelona Venzl<hi rend="sup">a</hi></placeName>
                                        <date>July 24<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1852</date>
                              </p>
                              <p><addressee>Isaac Leeser</addressee> Esqr.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <placeName>Philad P<hi rend="sup">a</hi>.</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">Rev<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. Sir!</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">There being so very few occurrences of this nature
                                        in this<lb/> part of the world, adding thereto your
                                        accustomed desire of obtaining<lb/> information concerning
                                        our people, has quite induced me to take<lb/> the liberty to
                                        encroach on your precious moments, with the object of<lb/>
                                        calling your attention to the late &amp; agreeable
                                        occurrences, which I trust<lb/> will prove interesting to
                                        those interested in the progress of the Jews<lb/> even
                                        amidst the most <sic>bigotted</sic> sect of
                                        christianity.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">We have often performed the ceremony of
                                                  <add>ברית</add> in the families<lb/> of
                                                  <persName>Messrs. is. Baiz</persName>,
                                                  <persName>M. H. Baiz</persName>, <persName>Is.
                                                  Valencia</persName>, <persName>Is. L
                                                  Lindo</persName>, <persName>A. H.
                                        Moron</persName>,<lb/> all of whom possess a numerous family
                                        &amp; resident of this place<lb/> The said ceremonies having
                                        been expected by <persName>Messrs. Is. Sass</persName> of
                                                  <placeName>St Thos.</placeName><lb/> &amp;
                                                  <persName>M F. Ricardo</persName> of
                                                  <placeName>Curacao</placeName>, both
                                                  <add>מוהל</add>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Our “progress” has been such, that we were lately
                                        obliged<lb/> to open a new <add>?</add>olio entitled
                                        “Marriages” where two young cou-<lb/>ples were enlisted
                                        &amp; another soon to follow.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Names of the Marr<hi rend="sup">d</hi>. Couples:
                                        in <date>Feby</date> last, <persName>Jb. Levy
                                                  Maduro</persName> to <persName>Miss
                                                  Jud.</persName><lb/>
                                        <persName>Jesn. Lindo</persName>; on the <date>19<hi
                                                  rend="sup">th</hi></date> inst, <persName>Michael
                                                  Perrso</persName> to <persName>Miss Reb.
                                                  Sasso.</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">For want of a better, I was honoured with the task
                                        of <add>חזן</add> which<lb/> was performed according to our
                                        rites, <persName>Mr. M. H. Buiz</persName> as V. C of the
                                                  <placeName>U. S. A.</placeName><lb/> certifying to
                                        the <sic>legallity</sic> of the said act. The attendance of
                                        the<lb/> natives, including the civil Authorities, were
                                        numerous in both<lb/> cases &amp; feel proud to add that the
                                        solemnity of the act has created<lb/> some sensations among
                                        the Goyims.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">The families &amp; Individuals residing here are:
                                                  <persName>Is. Baiz</persName> &amp; family</p>
                              <p rend="align(right)">over</p>
                              <pb n="2"/>
                              <p><persName>Is. Valencia</persName> &amp; family, <persName>M. H.
                                                  Baiz</persName> &amp; family; <persName>Is. Jes.
                                                  Lindo</persName> &amp; family; <persName>A.
                                                  H.<lb/> Moron</persName> &amp; family;
                                                  <persName>Michl. Perrso</persName> &amp; lady;
                                                  <persName>Abm. Jes Lindo</persName>,
                                                  <persName>Danl Delima</persName>.<lb/> (to be
                                        married to <persName>Miss Sar. Valencia</persName>)
                                                  <persName>Josiah L. Henriguez</persName>,
                                                  <persName>Mordy R. Caprilles</persName><lb/> &amp;
                                        myself beside a son of <persName>Mr. M H Baiz</persName> who
                                        is already over 13 years.,—you<lb/> will therefore observe
                                        that we complete full Minyan, even<lb/> for
                                                  <date>Kipur</date>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">Should you deem these Items worthy of occupying a
                                        space<lb/> in your valuable journal, I will feel most proud
                                        of having added to<lb/> your gen<hi rend="sup">l</hi>.
                                        Stock.   Meanwhile I subscribe myself</p>
                              <p rend="indent(7)">Revd. Sir! Your most Ob<hi rend="sup">t</hi>.</p>
                              <p rend="indent(9)">
                                        <persName role="author">Sam Piza</persName>
                              </p>
                              <pb n="3"/>
                              <p>The</p>
                              <p rend="indent(1)">
                                        <addressee>Revd. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(3)">
                                        <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p>politely recommended to <persName>Mr. Gershom Nathan</persName></p>
                              <p rend="indent(4)">
                                        <placeName>143 Canal St.</placeName>
                              </p>
                              <p rend="indent(5)">
                                        <placeName>
                                                  <hi rend="underline">New York</hi>
                                        </placeName>
                              </p>
